x4freetext: The target was made of tritium adsorbed in a thin
evaporated film of zirconium on a platinum backing. It
was 2.5 cm in diameter and 6 mg/cm2 thick an
approximate 1:1 ratio of tritium to zirconium
24 cm*24 cm NaI(Tl) crystal surrounded by a
plastic scintillator operated in anti-coincidence

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.148, p.211 (1970)

x4freetext: The errors shown (at the table and bars on
fig.) include statistics, uncertainties in the
least-square fitting, target thickness and
non-uniformity, and the error of the 3H(p,gamma)4He
comparison cross sections
The error in normalizing cross section to
the 3H(p,gamma)4He cross section. This error is
difficult to assess and could be as high as 20%.
Fits at forward angles were made with and without an
assumed neutron induced background; a discrepancy of
less than 10% is found. Hence, larger errors were
assigned to these points.
